            <scopecontent>
               <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                                 <p>This collection contains correspondence, diaries, pamphlets, advertisements, receipts, and illustrations related to Henry Baldridge.</p>
                                 <p>The correspondence includes personal letters from young women in Macon County and Decatur, Illinois, and business letters concerning Baldridge&#039;s activities as a salesman of Darby Gas Burners. In his diaries, he discusses courtship, social behavior, church programs, town and school activities, and weather.</p>
                                 <p>Lela E. Hoffman donated the collection to the Illinois Historical Survey in 1974.</p>
                        </scopecontent>
            


